  "title": "Tooling Engineer (Metal Stamping)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Collaborate with the toolmaking team to achieve departmental goals and objectives.</li>\n  <li>Provide technical tooling support to T&amp;D and production lines to meet technical and quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Support tool design and sales teams in fulfilling customer requirements.</li>\n  <li>Assist the tooling supervisor in ensuring tool readiness to support production schedules.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with production and planning teams to prioritize schedules based on tooling status.</li>\n  <li>Work with the Design department to improve tools for higher efficiency and output.</li>\n  <li>Lead the tooling team in problem-solving, identifying issues, and performing root cause analysis.</li>\n  <li>Drive and support continuous improvements in tooling and work processes.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with the toolroom on machining needs for tooling modifications and improvement programs.</li>\n  <li>Assist in managing the tooling group to optimize resource allocation and departmental performance.</li>\n  <li>Train, mentor, and guide toolmakers to enhance skills and capabilities.</li>\n  <li>Act on behalf of the Principal Engineer in their absence.</li>\n  <li>Perform any other duties as assigned by superiors or management.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
